{
  "texts": [
    "Integration of multi-omic datasetsTo unlock the synergy of multi-omic measurements, integrating the datasets with each other is necessary.",
    "This is a nontrivial task as the data generated by different modalities exist in entirely different feature spaces.",
    "When talking about integration, it is important to differentiate several scenarios.",
    "Argelaguet et al. [125] proposed three categories of integration tasks: Horizontal integration is used when the same modality is measured across different samples.",
    "An example could be the measurement of the spatial transcriptome across multiple myocardial infarction samples."
  ]
}